<h1>CSC 161 Module 0 Project: Uninterpretable Dance </h1>

<table width="100%">
<tr>
  <th align=left width="50%">Grading Form
  <th align=left width="50%">Name(s):
</tr>
</table>

<p>
This grading form expands the <a href="grading-form.pdf">Program
    Style Summary and Checklist</a> that applies to all program development
    in CSC 161.
</p>

<p>
This project will be worth 25 points, based on the following rubric:
</p>

<ul>
<li>
dance has at least 5 creative and unique dance sequence functions (5 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

<li>
dance is properly randomized (4 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
<li>
at least one function uses an array parameter (3 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
<li>
at least one function uses a pass-by-value parameter (3 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
<li>
at least one function uses a pass-by-reference parameter (6 points)
<ul>
<li>
pass-by-reference parameter used properly  (2 points)
<br><br><br><br>
<li>
value of pass-by-reference parameter changed  (2 points)
<br><br><br><br>
<li>
changed reference parameter used elsewhere in program  (2 points)
<br><br><br><br>
</ul>

<li>
Evidence of testing is included (4 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
<li>
Comments on Efficiency, Program Format, Comments, Readability, etc.
(Points not given, but points can be deducted.) 
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
</ul>

<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
<p>
Form updated:  23 January 2014
</p>

